        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 3:24PM CDT by NWS Topeka KS</headline>
        <description>At 324 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Kickapoo Reservation, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Horton, Everest, Whiting, Powhattan, Willis, and Kickapoo
Reservation.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
